{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> συλλύω</b>, <br /> <b>help in loosing</b>, ξύλλυε μητρὸς δεσμόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 723:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] — <i>middle</i>, τῷ Πριάμῳ συλλυσόμενοι τὸν παῖδ᾽ <b>assist</b> him <b>in redeeming.. </b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 678. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>solve difficulties, settle, put an end to</b>, τὰ νείκη, τὸν πόλεμον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 3.64, 29.22 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; σ. τινάς <b>reconcile</b> them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 7.21.8 (Megara, 2nd c.BC),compare “SIG” 599.13 (Priene, 2nd c.BC), “Klio” 18.281 (Delph., 2nd c.BC), 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 1.268 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; and so probably [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1317, εἰ μὴ ξυνάψων, ἀλλὰ συλλύσων πάρει\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] not to stir conflict, but <b>to reconcile</b>:— <i>middle</i> and <i>passive</i>, <b>come to a settlement</b>, πρός τινα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 12.4 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; τισι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Mac.13.47 \">LXX</a>]; ἐπὶ πᾶσι τοῖς δικαίοις[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.2Mac.11.14. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 294, δέχεσθαι δ᾽ οὔτε συλλύειν τινά, Scholia explanation συλλύειν by συγκλύειν (to be read συγκαταλύειν), συνοικεῖν\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], <b>rest under the same roof.</b>","strongNumber":"G21165","accentedUnicode":"συλλύω","shortDef":"rest under the same roof.","mediumDef":"rest under the same roof.","stepGloss":"to rest under the same roof.","stepTransliteration":"sulluō","count":0,"_step_Type":"